<paragraph id="F14CEB27110A26A68643A9F9E071A388" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="7484A8797CDBA4AFC8A559BBE4BD4D20" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schenodorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schenodorus benekenii" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benekenii">
<emphasis id="AFF08554987106F36A7A2B1B93B87DDA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Schenodorus benekenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9A88C0CCA3F36A0113BA6E7C38600DD6" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="263E6937AF886D998BC8CE69C5C2A83C" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6700AA1B6B3DCAE46FACF5E17ABABF84" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
The current widely used name 
<taxonomicName id="0CF0006C5B2132C4D13E0B9D84901915" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus benenkenii" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benenkenii">
<emphasis id="99C8566ADA794769CCE4C1EFE01B03BA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus benenkenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an implicit combination by 
<bibRefCitation id="0DC744BCCCB7417442557412B97A73FF" author="Trimen, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Botany, British and Foreign" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" pagination="329 - 334" refId="B32" refString="Trimen, H, 1872. Notes on some Scandinavian plants. Journal of Botany, British and Foreign 10: 329 - 334" title="Notes on some Scandinavian plants." volume="10" year="1872">Trimen (1872</bibRefCitation>
: 333) of the name described as 
<taxonomicName id="A63C75038F3A597C6C23D55EB2D7F823" authority="P.Beauv." authorityName="Lange" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schedonorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schedonorus benekenii" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benekenii">
<emphasis id="DCFA7542766FF0F0BCCCA6CE93A1217A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Schedonorus benekenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange 
<pageBreakToken id="922877812FA44BBC47A5B08A34E9D271" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" start="start">in</pageBreakToken>
Flora Danica. In the original publication, 
<bibRefCitation id="7528B0CA634666246B9688A0CA1D697B" author="Lange, J" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B20" refString="Lange, J, 1871. [Flora danica] Icones plantarum sponte nascentium in regnis Daniae et Norvegiae, in ducatibus Slesvici et Holsaticae, et in comitatibus Oldenburgi et Delmenhorstiae; ad illustrandum opus de iisdem plantis, regio jussu exarandum, Florae danicae nomine inscriptum 48: 5, t. 2826. 1871. Kjoebenhan. http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=4682&amp;Pagina=196" title="[Flora danica] Icones plantarum sponte nascentium in regnis Daniae et Norvegiae, in ducatibus Slesvici et Holsaticae, et in comitatibus Oldenburgi et Delmenhorstiae; ad illustrandum opus de iisdem plantis, regio jussu exarandum, Florae danicae nomine inscriptum 48: 5, t. 2826. 1871. Kjoebenhan. http: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / spa / Libro. php? Libro = 4682 &amp; Pagina = 196" year="1871">Lange (1871</bibRefCitation>
: 5) describes a perennial 
<taxonomicName id="FADA52B228BA8323DD0893C0BFAFC512" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A16B4F389BFFC2D2FDD6263E9CE871B0" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Bromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
living in forests, with nodding panicle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05307E890A421F6F914FB239CA53F13B" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
An exhaustive search to find the material 
<bibRefCitation id="86E3E2834B09DBDEF542181C2828FA2F" author="Lange, J" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B20" refString="Lange, J, 1871. [Flora danica] Icones plantarum sponte nascentium in regnis Daniae et Norvegiae, in ducatibus Slesvici et Holsaticae, et in comitatibus Oldenburgi et Delmenhorstiae; ad illustrandum opus de iisdem plantis, regio jussu exarandum, Florae danicae nomine inscriptum 48: 5, t. 2826. 1871. Kjoebenhan. http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/Libro.php?Libro=4682&amp;Pagina=196" title="[Flora danica] Icones plantarum sponte nascentium in regnis Daniae et Norvegiae, in ducatibus Slesvici et Holsaticae, et in comitatibus Oldenburgi et Delmenhorstiae; ad illustrandum opus de iisdem plantis, regio jussu exarandum, Florae danicae nomine inscriptum 48: 5, t. 2826. 1871. Kjoebenhan. http: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / spa / Libro. php? Libro = 4682 &amp; Pagina = 196" year="1871">Lange (1871)</bibRefCitation>
cites as models for the illustrations in table 2826 (figs 1, 2), finally had a result. The two syntypes are conserved in C in the Flora Danica subherbarium, that contains specimens drawn in the magnificent work &quot;Flora Danica&quot; (Olof Ryding pers. comm. 2018). Their labels state &quot;insula Lolland legit cl. E. Rostrup&quot; (C10021728)&quot; and &quot;Jonstrup Vang, legit cl. H. Mortensen&quot; (C10021729). Each folder indicates in handwriting that the specimens were drawn for &quot;Flora Danica&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EC7027B633D708D6315CDC41D190E7D" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
We choose as lectotype the latter sheet since its spikelets conserve most of its florets. The other sheet is in a more advanced phenological state and conserves, in most of its spikelets, only the glumes. The 
<taxonomicName id="2E845D09A8A1E6BBA91C75CC468834B5" family="Poaceae" genus="Rostrup" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rostrup" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="85E23A6A6B12D184EA95F9A4AA8ED684" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Rostrup</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen still conserves its basal part, with leaves, that is missing in the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9224EAB30FD1A52D6C9CC9D01110D0B9" ID-Zenodo-Dep="2702119" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.119.30254.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/297550" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph id="9E467DF18F11D31BFC2A2C43AEEC478F" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="C087B09BC253F70E60F338B523C70929" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Figure 3.</emphasis>
The original specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4E4BBDB28F40DA2DC1605D14A9ADAE54" authority="P.Beauv." authorityName="Lange" authorityYear="1871" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Schedonorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schedonorus benekenii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="benekenii">
<emphasis id="D3E6818BBD75392D180516ADF6C47601" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Schedonorus benekenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lange illustrated in Flora Danica (in table 2826, fig. 2) is the lectotype selected (C10021729). Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum of Denmark.
</paragraph>
</caption>
